          <tr><td><a href="/guides/old-orchard-beach-dispensary-guide/">Old Orchard Beach</a></td><td>5 miles</td><td>OOB Guide</td><td>Summer tourist traffic, seasonal revenue boost</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/guides/sanford-dispensary-guide/">Sanford</a></td><td>13 miles</td><td>Sanford Guide</td><td>York County regional hub, NH crossover traffic</td></tr>
          <tr><td><a href="/guides/portland-dispensary-guide/">Portland</a></td><td>15 miles</td><td>Portland Guide</td><td>Larger market, higher competition, premium positioning</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Early-entrant advantage:</strong> 2-3 competitors in a 22,000-person city with a university. The window is still open but closing.</li>
        <li><strong>University matters:</strong> 6,000+ UNE students bring predictable traffic patterns, price sensitivity, and evening demand. Extended hours and delivery near campus are competitive advantages.</li>
        <li><strong>Route 1 play:</strong> Lower rent, captures Saco and Sanford customers passing through. Downtown is for craft positioning; Route 1 is for volume.</li>
        <li><strong>Seasonal bonus:</strong> Old Orchard Beach is 5 miles away. Summer tourist traffic is incremental revenue, not your foundation.</li>
        <li><strong>Portland proximity:</strong> 15 miles away with 12+ stores. Your menu needs to be complete enough that Portland isn't a better option.</li>
        <li><strong>Total startup investment:</strong> $150,000-$350,000 to open and operate year one, depending on buildout and inventory choices.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the local licensing fee for a Biddeford cannabis dispensary?</summary>
        <p>The City of Biddeford charges approximately $2,000-2,500 annually for a local cannabis retail license. This is in addition to your Maine OCP state license fee ($500-$1,500 annually depending on license tier). Total annual licensing costs are approximately $2,500-$4,000 before opening.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I operate a cannabis delivery service from Biddeford?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Delivery is permitted for licensed adult-use dispensaries in Maine. A delivery operation based in Biddeford can serve customers throughout the Biddeford-Saco metro and into surrounding underserved towns like Hollis and Buxton. Delivery is especially valuable near the UNE campus where students may not have cars.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How many dispensaries can Biddeford support?</summary>
        <p>Biddeford (22,000 residents) currently has 2-3 dispensaries. Combined with Saco (20,000 residents, 3-4 dispensaries), the Biddeford-Saco metro has 5-7 stores for 40,000+ residents. For comparison, Portland (70,000 residents) has 12+. The market is underserved and can support additional operators, particularly with differentiated positioning.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What are the best neighborhoods for a Biddeford dispensary?</summary>
        <p>Main Street (downtown) offers walkability and university proximity — best for craft positioning. Elm Street provides good visibility on a commercial corridor. Route 1 captures through-traffic from Saco and Sanford — best for volume. Near UNE campus offers student traffic and evening demand — best for extended hours and delivery.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the typical startup cost for a Biddeford dispensary?</summary>
        <p>A typical 1,200-1,500 square foot buildout in Biddeford costs $120,000-$250,000. Combined with opening inventory ($25,000-$60,000), licensing fees ($2,500-$4,000), and working capital, total startup investment is $150,000-$350,000 before opening. Annual operating costs (rent, staff, security, utilities) run $130,000-$230,000.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

